{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-a98ad9f445f21242","input":{"filename":"rag-support-action-report.md","title":"RAG Support Search – Prioritized Action Report","markdown":"# Prioritized Action Report (RAG Support Search)\n\n**Prepared by:** RAG support search agent (ID: 33‑rag‑support‑search)\n\n---\n\n## Evidence Base\n\nThe analysis consulted the local operational records (via `analyze_records`). The top three records are:\n\n| ID | Title | Owner | Status | Impact | Risk | Summary |\n|----|-------|-------|--------|--------|------|---------|\n| **33‑A** | *RAG support search priority case* | Support | **urgent** | 52,461 | 5 | Retrieves grounded support answers from a document set. Highest‑impact open item. |\n| **33‑C** | *RAG support search blocked follow‑up* | Support | **blocked** | 24,963 | 4 | Blocked work requiring cross‑functional coordination before safe recommendation. |\n| **33‑B** | *RAG support search routine queue item* | Support | **in_review** | 12,729 | 1 | Lower‑risk operational item; useful for comparison and prioritization. |\n\n*Total records examined: 3* (risk score sum = 16; opportunity score sum = 10.8).\n\n---\n\n## Prioritization Rationale\n\n1. **Impact**: 33‑A has the highest impact (≈ 52 k) and is flagged *urgent*.\n2. **Risk**: 33‑C carries a moderate risk (4) but is *blocked*; clearing the blocker could unlock ~25 k impact.\n3. **Status**: 33‑B is already *in review* with low risk (1) – it should be completed after the higher‑impact items.\n\nThe combination of impact, risk, and current status yields the following ranking:\n\n1️⃣ **33‑A** – Immediate execution.\n2️⃣ **33‑C** – Resolve dependencies to unblock.\n3️⃣ **33‑B** – Continue review and close out.\n\n---\n\n## Action Items\n\n| Priority | Action | Owner | Due (approx.) | Dependencies |\n|----------|--------|-------|---------------|--------------|\n| **1** | **Execute the urgent RAG support search case** – finalize the implementation, run end‑to‑end tests, and deploy to production. | Support team lead | 1 week | Completion of prerequisite data‑set validation (already done). |\n| **2** | **Unblock the follow‑up** – identify the cross‑functional stakeholder (e.g., security or compliance), schedule a coordination call, and obtain the required sign‑off. | Support + Security liaison | 2 weeks | Stakeholder availability; risk mitigation plan. |\n| **3** | **Close the routine queue item** – finish the in‑review assessment, document findings, and archive the record. | Support analyst | 3 weeks | None; depends on capacity after higher priorities. |\n\n---\n\n## Assumptions & Uncertainties\n\n- The record data reflects the current state; no recent changes are missing.\n- No external constraints (e.g., budget, staffing) override the suggested timeline.\n- The “blocked” status for **33‑C** is due solely to a missing coordination step; no deeper technical impediment is present.\n\nIf any of these assumptions prove false, re‑prioritization may be required.\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Notify** the support lead of the prioritized actions (via existing communication channel).\n2. **Assign** owners to each action and record due dates in the project tracker.\n3. **Monitor** progress weekly; update the record statuses accordingly.\n\n---\n\n*Report generated automatically from local dossier and record analysis.*"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:20:59.810Z"}}
